ii —The holotype GR.731 has four whorls of spines in the Zenker organ. This has to be considered as a malformation: although in the Candoninae most of the formation process of the Zenker organ takes places after the moult to adulthood, the number of whorls remains constant in adults (
Yamada et al. 2014
). The paratype GR.730 bears seven whorls, as typical for the subfamily.
